<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Caroline Hilhorst I agree that Christianity is not a going to church on Sunday thing, but Christ in you, the hope of Glory! It is allowing Jesus to li<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Caroline Hilhorst I agree that Christianity is not a going to church on Sunday thing, but Christ in you, the hope of Glory! It is allowing Jesus to live His life through us as us. BUT Jesus adds us to a local body where He is the head, and in that local body we need to live out His kind of life with people we grow to love, with people we don't even like, etc. It is living in the body that we grow to maturity, to the full stature of Jesus.<br /><br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
